1. User registers в†’ password hashed by bcrypt в†’ saved to MongoDB

2. User logs in в†’
   - Server creates access token (15 min, returned in response body)
   - Server creates refresh token (7 days, sent as HttpOnly cookie)
   - Frontend stores access token in localStorage

3. User searches "London" в†’
   - Axios interceptor adds: Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>
   - Backend auth middleware verifies JWT signature
   - Rate limiter checks: has this IP made 100 requests in 15 min?
   - Weather controller checks Redis: is "weather:london" cached?
   - Cache MISS в†’ calls OpenWeatherMap в†’ stores in Redis 10 min
   - Returns weather data

4. 15 minutes later, access token expires в†’
   - Next API call gets 403
   - Axios response interceptor catches it automatically
   - Silently calls /api/auth/refresh
   - Browser sends HttpOnly refresh token cookie automatically
   - Server validates, rotates refresh token, returns new access token
   - Original request is retried вЂ” user never notices

5. User logs out в†’
   - Refresh token deleted from MongoDB
   - Cookie cleared
   - Access token removed from localStorage